The paper deals with communication complexity and Boolean functions, which are typically studied in the sub-category cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of Fourier sparsity and spectral norm suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and linear algebra (cs.DS). The structural results about Boolean functions also suggest a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
